    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "ok so if those micro-cracks are spreading through the internal part of the slab where we cant see them, does that mean the structural integrity is just secretly degrading even if the surface looks fine? like how do engineers actually monitor those \"hidden\" internal stresses or cracks when they are deep inside the solid mass?",
