      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Yes, that's exactly right; the structural integrity is degrading internally even if the surface appears fine, which is a classic problem in materials science. To monitor these internal stresses, engineers use various non-destructive testing (NDT) methods. Techniques like ultrasonic pulse velocity or ground-penetrating radar (GPR) can map out internal voids, delaminations, or areas of reduced material quality deep within the concrete mass. These methods allow inspectors to \"see\" the hidden damage before it becomes critical.",
      "source": "target",
